  "bib_entries": {
    "118919276": {
      "title": "A nonstandard finite-difference scheme for the Lotka-Volterra system",
      "abstract": "Most numerical integration schemes for the Lotka-Volterra system have the property that the computed solutions spiral when in fact the actual solutions are periodic corresponding to closed curves. We show that a direct application of the nonstandard methods of Mickens allows the construction of a finite-difference scheme that is dynamically consistent with the differential equations. Numerical results are given to support this result."
